<UL>
<LI><B>Needed libraries:</B>
	<A href="ftp://ftp.gtk.org/pub/gtk/">glib/gtk+</A> 1.2.0 or newer!
	Note: You can check this with the command 'gtk-config --version',
	don't use version 1.2.4, seems to be problematic with xap.
	<P>
<LI><B>Download:</B>
	Get the current
	<A href="/~rasca/xap-_VERSION_.tar.gz">source code</A>
	of <EM>xap</EM> and <EM>xwf</EM> via HTTP or
	first checkout the <A href=ChangeLog>ChangeLog</A> to see what has changed
	since the last release. For a RPM package have a look at Romildo's ftp
	site <A href=ftp://urano.iceb.ufop.br/pub/xap/>ftp://urano.iceb.ufop.br/pub/xap/</A>
	<P>
<LI><B>Installation:</B>
	see the <A href=INSTALL>INSTALL</A> document ..
<P>
<LI><EM><font color=red>xap</font></EM><BR>
<A href="docs/desktop.png"><img alt="[screendump-xap]" src=docs/xap.png width=266 height=48 align=right></A>
	Usage:
	<code>xap [-v] [-t] [-g &lt;geom&gt;]</code>
	<P>
	<EM>xap</EM> looks for a directory named '$HOME/.xap'. For every included
	subdirectoy a notebook page is created in the GUI. Every symbolic
	link in this subdirectories will result in an application button
	to start this application or to drop file names which will be
	passed as arguments while launching this program.
	<P>
	A <EM>Drag and Drop</EM> of an application to the label of a notebook-page
	will create a new program button. Use mouse button 3 over a program-button
	to rename or delete a button.
	<P>
<LI><EM><font color=red>xwf</font></EM><BR>
<A href=docs/xwf.png>
<img alt="[screendump-xwf]" src=docs/xwf_small.png width=180 height=258 align=right>
</A>
	Usage:
	<code>xwf [-v] [directory] [-g &lt;geom&gt;]</code><BR>
	For a short description of the <EM>xwf</EM> application and
	a list of the keyboard short cuts look inside the included
	man-page.
	<P>
<LI><EM><font color=red>xpg</font></EM><BR>
	Usage:
	<CODE>xpg [files ..]</CODE>
	<P>
